# Adding a feature: l10n + usecase + test

Every new user-facing feature or behavior change MUST satisfy all three. PRs
missing any of these are incomplete.

## 1. l10n — no hardcoded user-facing strings

Any text shown to the user goes through `AppLocalizations`, with keys added to
**both** `lib/l10n/app_en.arb` and `lib/l10n/app_zh.arb`, then regenerated.

```dart
// BAD: hardcoded, breaks zh/en switching
Text('No tasks')

// GOOD
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.emptyTasks)
```

After editing ARB files, regenerate: `flutter gen-l10n` (or `flutter pub get`).
Keep `app_en.arb` and `app_zh.arb` key sets in sync — every key in one exists in
the other.

## 2. usecase — business logic lives in `domain/`, not widgets

New behavior that touches data goes in a `*UseCase` under
`lib/features/<feature>/domain/`, exposed via a Riverpod `*UseCaseProvider`, and
called from the presentation layer. Do not call repositories/services directly
from widgets.

`presentation/` and `domain/` MUST NOT import `data/` or `platform/` — depend on
`core/contracts` interfaces only (enforced by `tool/check_layer_imports.sh`).

## 3. test — cover the new logic

- Use cases / notifiers / pure logic → unit test under `test/unit/...`.
- Widgets / pages → widget test (and golden where it already exists) under
  `test/widget/...`.
- Mirror the `lib/` path in `test/`. Run `flutter test` before committing.
- Coverage thresholds (`tool/check_coverage.dart`): domain ≥ 90%, data ≥ 80%.
